Observational Techniques:

Ground-Based Observations: Employ advanced ground-based telescopes for high-resolution imaging and spectroscopy.
Space-Based Observations: Utilize orbiting observatories to overcome atmospheric limitations and capture clearer astronomical data.
Radio and Microwave Observation: Investigate celestial objects through radio and microwave frequencies for unique perspectives.

Computational Approaches:

Big Data Analytics: Develop algorithms for the analysis of massive datasets generated by modern telescopes.
Simulations: Conduct numerical simullations to modal complex astrophysical processes and validate observational findings.
Quantum Computing Applications: Explore the potential of quantum computing in solving computationally intensive problems in astrophysics.

